      "writtenOn": "2018-11-20T03:01:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Current MoveFile matches the behavior of \"mv\".\n\nCurrent CopyFile matches the behavior of \"cp --preserve\u003dmode\". The default \"cp\" command works just as it creates the destination file with the default way (affected by umask).\n\n [nya@bep cptmp]% ls -l\n total 0\n -rwxrwxrwx 1 root adm 0 Nov 20 11:40 a\n [nya@bep cptmp]% (umask 002; cp a b)\n [nya@bep cptmp]% ls -l\n total 0\n -rwxrwxrwx 1 root adm          0 Nov 20 11:40 a\n -rwxrwxr-x 1 nya  primarygroup 0 Nov 20 11:43 b\n\nBut I\u0027m not sure if the default \"cp\" behavior is what users of this function expect. I think it\u0027s fine to define our own behavior, rather than mimicing cp/mv, as long as it\u0027s explicitly documented. Then I slightly prefer matching the behavior of MoveFile/CopyFile...",
